The Timeless Grandeur of Carcassonne: A Tale of History, Heroes, and Hope In the heart of the Languedoc region in the south of France, where the languid Aude River meanders through the rolling hills, there stands a testament to time, a jewel of medieval grandeur, a castle and walled city that have witnessed centuries of history and countless stories. This is the enchanting tale of Carcassonne. A Castle Born of History Carcassonne, whose origins date back to the Roman era, is a name that resonates with history. But it wasn't until the 12th century that it truly began to weave its destiny into the annals of time. It was then that the Visigoths, a Germanic people, fortified the hill where Carcassonne now stands, laying the foundation for the castle and walled city that would become legendary. As the medieval world swirled with political intrigues and religious fervor, Carcassonne became a pivotal player in the tumultuous events of the Albigensian Crusade. This conflict, rooted in religious schisms and political power struggles, pitted the Catholic Church against the Cathars, a Christian sect deemed heretical by the papal authority. The formidable walls of Carcassonne bore witness to one of the most dramatic episodes in its history. In 1209, when the Crusaders arrived, led by Simon de Montfort, the city and its inhabitants found themselves trapped in a harrowing siege that would last for more than a year. Despite the odds stacked against them, the defenders of Carcassonne displayed unyielding courage and resilience. The Defenders of Carcassonne Among these defenders was Dame Carcas, a name that has since become an emblem of Carcassonne's indomitable spirit. The story goes that as the city endured the relentless siege, its supplies began to dwindle. Desperation loomed, but Dame Carcas, a woman of unshakable resolve, devised a cunning plan. She gathered the remaining food in the city, which amounted to little more than a single pig and a small sack of grain. Dame Carcas, in a display of defiance that would be remembered for centuries, had the pig fattened and then hurled it over the city walls, landing with a resounding thud before the besieging Crusaders. The sight of a seemingly well-provisioned city spurred rumors that Carcassonne still had ample resources. The Crusaders, believing they faced a futile task, eventually lifted the siege. Dame Carcas became a symbol of the city's tenacity, and it is said that her name, combined with the Occitan word for "ring" (cassa), gave birth to the name "Carcassonne." Whether this is true or merely a romanticized legend, it is a testament to the power of human spirit and the ingenuity that can arise in times of great adversity. The Splendor of Medieval Architecture Walking through the cobbled streets of Carcassonne today, one is transported to the medieval world. The castle and walled city are a time capsule, preserving the architectural grandeur of centuries past. The outer walls, punctuated by towering watchtowers and fortified gates, wrap around the city like a protective embrace. These walls, constructed primarily in the 13th century, stand as a testament to the military prowess of the time. As you trace their formidable path, you can almost feel the echoes of countless sentinels who once patrolled the ramparts, their eyes fixed on the horizon in vigilant defense. The inner city is a labyrinth of narrow streets, alleys, and squares. Each stone tells a story, each corner whispers secrets from the past. The Basilica of Saint-Nazaire, a Gothic masterpiece, rises majestically within the walls, its stained glass windows flooding the interior with a kaleidoscope of colors. Its vaulted ceilings and intricately carved choir stalls stand as a testament to the medieval craftsmanship that once flourished here. A Place of Refuge and Culture Carcassonne was not just a fortress; it was also a place of culture and refinement. The medieval courts of the Trencavel lords who ruled over Carcassonne were known for their patronage of troubadours, the poets and minstrels who sang of love and chivalry. It was a time when art and literature flourished within these walls, amidst the backdrop of siege and strife. One of the most famous troubadours associated with Carcassonne was Bernard de Ventadour, whose verses celebrated courtly love and the ideals of chivalry. His songs echoed through the courtyards, providing solace and inspiration to those who sought refuge within the city. The Renaissance and Restoration As the centuries rolled on, Carcassonne's fortunes ebbed and flowed. It suffered the ravages of war, fell into disrepair, and faced the threat of demolition during the French Revolution. However, its enduring beauty and historical significance could not be forgotten. text: Today, Israel declared a state of war following thousands of rockets launched by militant organisation Hamas. This escalation follows months of increasing violence in the Israeli-Palestinian conflict, with a level of casualties in the occupied West Bank not seen in years. In an unprecedented move, militants infiltrated southern Israeli towns using motorcycles, SUVs, and paragliders. Videos circulating on social media depict militants firing at civilians in Israel's southern towns. One video, filmed by a resident in Sderot, captures Hamas militants firing at civilian cars on the street. The resident recorded the video from his terrace and is seen hastily taking cover as a gunman briefly looks in his direction. There are also reports, including videos from Gaza, showing militants dragging the bodies of several Israeli soldiers onto the streets in celebration. This surge in violence comes a day after Hamas, which governs Gaza, stated that the "people had to draw a line to end the occupation" and accused Israel of continuing to commit crimes, particularly at the holy site of Al-Aqsa in Jerusalem. In a pre-recorded speech, Hamas militant leader Mohamed Deif declared, "We have decided to put an end to all of this, with the help of God, so that the enemy understands that the time of recklessness without accountability is over. We declare Operation Al-Aqsa Flood, and the first strike has surpassed 5,000 missiles and shells in the first 20 minutes." Kenya joins the rest of the world in solidarity with the State of Israel and unequivocally condemn terrorism and attacks on innocent civilians in the country. The people of Kenya and their government hereby express deepest sympathy and send condolences to the families of all victims. We also wish a speedy recovery to the injured. Kenya strongly maintains that there exists no justification whatsoever for terrorism, which constitutes a serious threat to international peace and security. All acts of terrorism and violent extremism are abhorrent, criminal and unjustifiable, regardless of the perpetrator, or their motivations. The international community must mobilise to bring the perpetrators, organizers, financiers, sponsors, supporters and enablers of these reprehensible criminal acts of terrorism to account and speedily bring them to justice. In consideration of the complex and delicate context of the security situation in Israel-Palestine, Kenya also makes a call for the de-escalation of violence and urges all parties to restrain from further military action, given its potential to intensify carnage and the suffering of innocent civilians, and to trigger heightened tension in the region and beyond. We are profoundly disturbed that civilians continue to be intentionally targeted in this conflict, as a consequence of which the number of casualties continues to rise. We therefore call on all parties to respect the rights of civilians and honour their obligations under international law. Finally, we take this opportunity to reiterate our firm stand in solidarity with all those calling on the parties to desist from further attacks, promptly effect cease-fire and embark on a path towards a peaceful resolution of the conflict.

Ayinla Omowura: Life And Times Of An Apala Legend This book is a narrative of the life and times of one of the most profound and unarguably, one of the most original Yoruba musicians of post-colonial Nigeria. Murdered in a barroom brawl in Abeokuta, Ogun State in 1980, Ayinla Omowura, forty years after his untimely passage, has refused to die, both in the consciousness of the people of southwest Nigeria, even elsewhere, as well as in the hearts and on the lips of the people. The book plots the graph of Omowura‚Äôs youth, his musicality, family, the fatality of his early departure, and events that led to his death. From the lens of family, friends, his songs, and relics of people who interfaced with him while alive, a narrative is constructed here about the short life of music and society that Ayinla lived. He was a lay scholar, an ombudsman, autodidact, and carrier of the cultural burden of his Yoruba people. Having tasted life in pre and post-colony, the latter being a time when there was beginning to appear noticeable conflicts between traditional life and modernity, Ayinla taught with his music that the latter could only exist if the values of the former are embedded into it. Having lived a rough life at youth and now, thrust to the top of society by fame and cash in his later life, Ayinla never recovered from the conflict this posed. He didn‚Äôt really realize the enormous roles expected of his catapult to the top of high society. This, in part, was responsible for his early tragic exit. On this date in 1984, PREFAB SPROUT released the single, WHEN LOVE BREAKS DOWN, (October 7th, 1984). Prefab Sprout's second studio album was a shimmering jazz-pop masterpiece distinguished by Paddy's witty and inventive songwriting. The album, carrying a duration of 45 minutes and 22 seconds, traverses a myriad of human weaknesses such as regret, lust, and infidelity, all explored with cynical insight and sarcastic flair‚Äã‚Äã. One track that stood out was "When Love Breaks Down," the band's first of seven UK Top 40 hits and a song that marked their first chart appearance in the United States. "When Love Breaks Down" is a reflection of Paddy's romantic experiences and is characterized by a bittersweet and poignant mood. Phil Thornalley, a former member of the Cure, produced this song, marking it as the only track on the album not produced by Thomas Dolby. The radio-friendly production and emotionally resonant lyrics made this song one of the most straightforward and heartfelt that Paddy had written to that point in his career‚Äã‚Äã. Despite the individual success of "When Love Breaks Down," the album "Steve McQueen" only managed a #21 spot in the album charts. Nonetheless, the album's refined and sophisticated tone did not go unnoticed, and it ultimately made the NME‚Äôs list of the best hundred LPs ever made. The album was titled "Steve McQueen" in all countries except for the United States, where it was named "Two Wheels Good" due to a legal conflict with the estate of the American actor Steve McQueen. In a 2009 interview with Mojo magazine, Paddy was critical of one line in "When Love Breaks Down," namely "absence makes the heart lose weight." He felt it was "prissy, glib, too thought out." Despite this self-criticism, "When Love Breaks Down" remains a popular song that has been covered by numerous artists, including the Zombies, E'voke, Kate Walsh, Lisa Stansfield, Portastatic, Snow Patrol, and Nerina Pallot‚Äã‚Äã. The B-side to the original single release was "Diana," which was later re-recorded and included on the album "Protest Songs" in 1989‚Äã‚Äã. PREFAB SPROUT PADDY McALOON was an anomalous character amidst the pop climate of the '80s who applied himself to the craft of songwriting with the devotion of his heroes, songwriters like Brian Wilson, Burt Bacharach and Stephen Sondheim. Following a period studying English at Newcastle, he formed Prefab Sprout and together produced a torrent of compelling songs that found inspiration in sources as diverse as George Gershwin, The Beatles and Steely Dan. On Swoon, the debut album recorded in 1983, tracks like ‚ÄòTechnique‚Äô, ‚ÄòCruel‚Äô and ‚ÄòElegance‚Äô were dazzling discourses on love and loss. Accused by ill-minded hacks of a high and mighty cleverness, almost intellectual snobbery, Prefab Sprout pushed on and released a second album, Steve McQueen, in 1985. Produced by pop guru Thomas Dolby, the record was a collection of sophisticated and life-affirming songs that brushed the line between heartbreak and recovery, and captured the essence of both, all with an added self-absorbed sting. Suffering a similar fate to the singles it spawned, not to mention the several attempts to push the gorgeous ‚ÄòWhen Love Breaks Down‚Äô into the Top Twenty, ‚ÄòSteve McQueen‚Äô only managed a #21 spot in the album charts; but some consolation perhaps came when it made the NME‚Äôs list of the best hundred LPs ever made. In an interview with the October 2009 edition of Mojo magazine, McAloon was critical of one of this song's lines. He said: "I became very conscious of other people making hit records and I wanted to be there with Frankie Goes to Hollywood and Scritti Politti. It would be nice to have a song the milkman could whistle, I like the glory of language, the gag."

On this date in 1975, Timothy David Minchin was born in Northampton, England, to Australian parents. On his website he describes himself as a ‚Äúcomedian, actor, composer, songwriter, pianist, musical director and huge rock 'n' roll megastar.‚Äù He grew up in Perth, Australia, where he attended the University of Western Australia and received a bachelor of arts in English and theater in 1995. He went on to obtain an advanced degree in contemporary music at the Conservatorium of Western Australia in 1998. In 2002 he began his career as a musical comedian in Melbourne in shows where he sang original songs while accompanying himself on piano and incorporating more traditional stand-up elements. Minchin came to prominence at the Melbourne International Comedy Festival in 2005 and went on to win the Perrier Newcomer Award at the Edinburgh Fringe Festival that same year. Living in London, he toured the United Kingdom, Australia, New Zealand and North America. He has also written the book and lyrics for the Royal Shakespeare Company's adaptation of Roald Dahl's "Matilda," which premiered in Stratford-upon-Avon in December 2010. Minchin is outspoken in his opposition to religion and to nonscientific claims made by New Age groups and others. His comedy and songs cover a wide range of topics, from love and sex to political controversies and language use, but a primary focus is on religion. Many contain strong language but some are safe for radio play, including ‚ÄúPeace Anthem for Palestine,‚Äù which Minchin says sums up his views on religious conflict: ‚ÄúWe don't eat pigs, you don't eat pigs, it seems it's been that way forever. So if you don't eat pigs and we don't eat pigs, why not not eat pigs together?‚Äù He does express fondness for the music of his upbringing in the Anglican Church and the secular and family aspects of Christmas in the Southern Hemisphere in his 2009 single ‚ÄúWhite Wine in the Sun.‚Äù But its hard-hitting lyrics created a firestorm in Australia when the song was released as part of a charitable seasonal album in 2010. Themes of his work include his contempt for unscientific thinking ("If You Open Your Mind Too Much Your Brain Will Fall Out (Take My Wife)‚Äù and for the beauty of scientific thinking in the comedy routine ‚ÄúTony the Fish.‚Äù Minchin returned to touring in 2019 after a seven-year break. The BACK tour visited Australia and New Zealand in March and April, with performances scheduled in October and November in Europe. FIB COMMANDER BRIGADIER ALFRED MATAMBO VISITS KENYA QUICK REACTION FORCE SERVING UNDER MONUSCO IN BENI DRC In a gesture of solidarity and support, the Force Intervention Brigade (FIB) Commander, Brigadier Alfred Matambo, paid a significant visit to the Kenyan Quick Reaction Force (QRF) deployed under the United Nations Stabilization Mission in the Democratic Republic of Congo (MONUSCO) in Beni. This visit underscores the critical role played by international peacekeepers in promoting stability and security in the troubled region. The Democratic Republic of Congo, particularly the volatile eastern provinces, has been plagued by a long-standing conflict, characterized by militia activities, inter-ethnic violence, and the illicit exploitation of natural resources. The FIB, consisting of troops from various contributing countries, has been a crucial element of MONUSCO's efforts to restore peace and security in this tumultuous region. Brigadier Matambo, a seasoned military strategist and leader, arrived in Kenya QRF Base in Beni to assess the operational readiness and morale of the troops, which has been at the forefront of MONUSCO's efforts in countering armed groups and providing humanitarian assistance to the affected population. During his visit, he commended the Kenyan troops for their dedication and unwavering commitment to the mission's objectives. In a meeting with Kenyan QRF commanders, Brigadier Matambo emphasized the importance of coordinated efforts among MONUSCO forces and the need for adaptability in the face of evolving security challenges. He stated, "Our mission is not only to protect the people of the Democratic Republic of Congo but also to help create conditions for lasting peace. Your role here is crucial, and your sacrifices are not unnoticed." The Kenyan QRF, known for their rapid response capabilities, has been instrumental in thwarting attacks, protecting civilians, and providing critical medical aid to the wounded. They have also been involved in community engagement initiatives aimed at fostering trust and cooperation with local communities, a pivotal aspect of peacekeeping in conflict zones. Brigadier Matambo's visit serves as a testament to the international community's commitment to the peace and stability of the Democratic Republic of Congo. The FIB's presence, along with dedicated troop contributions from nations like Kenya, plays a pivotal role in stabilizing the region and creating an environment conducive to the political and socio-economic development that the Congolese people so desperately need. As Brigadier Matambo concludes his visit to Beni, he reaffirms the FIB's unwavering commitment to its mission and expresses gratitude to all peacekeepers, including the Kenyan QRF, for their dedication and sacrifices in pursuit of a peaceful and prosperous Democratic Republic of Congo. The international community continues to stand united in its quest to bring an end to the suffering of the Congolese people and pave the way for a brighter future in the region. https://bit.ly/3RRrdGU:=:https://mod.go.ke/news/fib-commander-brigadier-alfred-matambo-visits-kenya-quick-reaction-force-serving-under-monusco-in-beni-drc/

Don't expect corporate outlets to challenge establishment perspectives or remedy double standards. Their obedience is a given. These biases intensify the ongoing tragedies. text: We're back with 5 facts about Hoederer you must know before you claim him as husbando (Nah you can't, he has wife and a child) 1. A multi melee user and also an Arts user Besides a dagger and a sword, Hoederer is also seen carrying a crossbow on his back. After pretending to be part of the Kazdel Royal Court boyband, Hoederer discards the crossbow and acquires a new sword likely given by Manfred. In his playable form, Hoederer wields a larger new sword while keeping his dagger. Hoederer mostly known only as a mele fighter relying on pure combat abilities, turns out he can also use Originium Arts, a fact not even W knew despite them being comrades for years. It's unknown why Hoederer rarely uses his Arts. Before W learns about it in chapter 12 only Ines knew about Hoederer's Arts and called it as Embers. 2. He is unexpectedly a bookworm Mercenary Sarkaz has always been associated with fighting, not least the Darknights trio: W, Ines, and Hoederer. Of the three, Hoederer is probably the least resembling a Sarkaz, even Ines who is cosplaying as Sarkaz looks more like one than him, why? Hoederer always prioritizes dialogue in conflict as much as possible, he always blames himself if things don't go according to plan, always feels uncomfortable after killing to the point that his hands will tremble, and most importantly he likes to read, collect, and write books! Hoederer wrote a book titled "History of Sarkaz Warfare" that Manfred lent to Paprika, and it's implied that the book titled "Struggle and Freedom" mentioned in W's archive is also his work. If W likes to cook potatoes, Ines has knitting as hobby, then Hoederer is a bookworm. 3. Lost his left eye in order to gain Manfred's trust. After getting an order from Theresis to lead his merc group to Londinium, Hoederer made a plan with W and Ines to reveal and undermine Theresis' plan to keep him from seizing any more power, he helped to fake Ines' death so she could freely work as a spy in the shadows under the guise of a Messenger. Still everything in Victoria is beyond Hoederer's expectation, he was put under house arrest by Theresis, so Hoederer carried out a new plan to gain Manfred's trust so he could roaming around Londinium which would later help Rhodes Island's operation in Londinium. Hoederer told W that he had killed Ines to gain Manfred's trust and lost his left eye as a heavy price to pay, of course by now we know it was all a stageplay that the two had planned. 4. Hoederer killed Scout Yes, Scout was an old comrade of W, Ines, and Hoederer during Babel days. It is said that outside of W and Hoederer, Scout was the first person to gain Ines' trust. Scout was someone respected by W, so why did Hoederer killed Scout? Scout's death was a necessary sacrifice. It was almost impossible for the entire Doctor rescue team to survive Chernobog, so to ensure their survival, Scout made a pact with W. Scout would fight and kill Garcin, the leader of Sarkaz mercenaries aligned with Theresi, with Garcin's death, W could replace Garcin and take control of both the Sarkaz mercenaries from Reunion as well as from Theresis. In return, W would make sure the Doctor's rescue team safely leave Chernobog. After dealing with Garcin, Scout caused a commotion in the core city of Chernobog to distract Reunion's attention from the rescue team. Hoederer and Ines didn't want to kill him and would've preferred to let him go quietly, however, his actions were drawing too much attention from the Reunion forces, so they had no choice but to kill him to maintain the appearance of loyalty to Reunion. Pretty sure he can be justified right? 5. Is it true Hoederer simping for vtuber Eureka? At the April Fool 2023 event when Eureka was managing a stream, there was one viewer with username One Patched Intel who was implied to be Hoederer, the funniest part was that people weren't sure if he would survive in Victoria arc before chapter 12, but since the "One Patched Intel" was very chatty during the stream that would take place after the event, players took it as confirmation that Hoederer survived. Regardless, there is no further confirmation until his archives are accessible tomorrow and April Fool's story cannot be considered a canon plot since Haimao literally made a cameo there. Bonus: His name seems to be a reference to a central character in the French stageplay Les mains sales by Jean-Paul Sartre. Parts of Darknights' Memoir and its related characters' stories thematically parallel it, and Hoederer himself shares a number of details with Sartre's Hoederer, a man with a trusting nature who wants a free society, is targeted by many people, and even remains friendly with two people after his head. ----

Maliwanag na tama ang ating ginagawa, tama ang ating mga strategy at tama ang ating pag-apply ng NTF-ELCAC. Hintayin ko ang imbitasyon ninyo na makablik ako dito sa 3ID para ideklara ang area na ito - insurgent free. Hintayin ko yan. Go ahead. Keep up the good work. Keep working. We will get there in the end. Well done to all you. Congratulations.‚Äù These were the meaningful but rather challenging words of the President during his ‚ÄúTalk to the Troops‚Äù led by no less than Major General Marion R Sison, Commander of 3ID. Also present during the activity were all the Brigade Commanders, Battalion Commanders and more than 300 personnel and Civilian Human Resource of 3ID. Earlier, the Spearhead Troopers met the President's arrival with a warm reception and rendered him with military honors. MGen Sison also gave the President an overview of the 3ID's accomplishments, highlighting the dismantling of the remaining Guerrilla Fronts from eight (8) active in 2018 to three (3) weakened as of the period. A total of 118 Captured, Confiscated, Surrendered and Recovered (CCSR) firearms from various operations conducted against the Communist Terrorist Group (CTG) from 01 January 2023 to 06 October 2023 were also presented to the President. For the period covered, 3ID recorded a total of 73 armed encounters, with six (6) Major Engagements that resulted in the neutralization of 137 CTG personalities, of whom 11 were High Value Individuals (HVIs). In his message, MGen Sison conveyed his gratitude to the President and the Commander in Chief for recognizing the dedicated efforts and achievements of 3ID. Today, October 7, the church celebrates the yearly feast of Our Lady of the Rosary. SATURDAY, 7 OCTOBER TEXT: PROVERBS 13:1-11 TOPIC: A WISE SON (1) TEXT Proverbs 13:1-11 [1]A wise child accepts a parent‚Äôs discipline; a mocker refuses to listen to correction. [2]Wise words will win you a good meal, but treacherous people have an appetite for violence. [3]Those who control their tongue will have a long life; opening your mouth can ruin everything. [4]Lazy people want much but get little, but those who work hard will prosper. [5]The godly hate lies; the wicked cause shame and disgrace. [6]Godliness guards the path of the blameless, but the evil are misled by sin. [7]Some who are poor pretend to be rich; others who are rich pretend to be poor. [8]The rich can pay a ransom for their lives, but the poor won‚Äôt even get threatened. [9]The life of the godly is full of light and joy, but the light of the wicked will be snuffed out. [10]Pride leads to conflict; those who take advice are wise. [11]Wealth from get-rich-quick schemes quickly disappears; wealth from hard work grows over time. [NLT] INSPIRATION A son is considered wise when he accepts the good advice or teachings of his parents because no good parents will ever mislead their child. Therefore, in Proverbs 13:1-11, the all-knowing God gives us, His children, some pieces of advice and wise is that son who heeds these instructions. In vs.3, God expects us to exercise self-control over our speech and master our tongue for words have the ability to cut and destroy (James 3:6). If you want to have self-control, begin with your tongue. If you can control this small but powerful part of your body, then you can control the rest of your body. God also instructs us to live blameless lives as it safeguards and brings a greater sense of order to our lives. QUESTION: Are you a wise or foolish son? PRAYER: Oh God, help me to be/a wise son who listens to both his earthly and heavenly parents instructions, in Jesus name. Amen.

# **SIXTY YEARS ON: *‚ÄúThe Birds"*** **By *Ray Cunneff*** **October 7, 2023** **I first saw Alfred Hitchcock‚Äôs ‚ÄúThe Birds‚Äù at the Sutton Theater in Manhattan in 1963. The theater was on the east side, my apartment on the west side, and I had to walk through Central Park to get home. There were birds everywhere in the park and I was a bit freaked out, having never looked at birds in quite the same way.** **That was sixty years ago. I was a nineteen year old page at NBC at 30 Rock, not long before leaving for Europe with NBC‚Äôs ‚ÄúInternational Showtime‚Äù. I had moonlighted as a production assistant on the New York locations for MGM‚Äôs ‚ÄúSunday in New York‚Äù with Rod Taylor and Jane Fonda, but never actually met him. (I did meet Jane Fonda by a rowboat in Central Park, worried about her hair should it capsize.)** **As I‚Äôve written elsewhere, I had become a lifelong fan of Rod Taylor, first with George Pal‚Äôs classic ‚ÄúThe Time Machine‚Äù, but then 20th Century Fox‚Äôs mostly forgotten ABC TV series ‚ÄúHong Kong‚Äù. Rod was so good at accents, from upper-class British, to southern gentleman, to Bronx boxer, to American leading man, that few people knew he was Australian - the most famous Aussie since Errol Flynn.** **But as I‚Äôve also written, ‚ÄúThe Birds‚Äù was an affirmation of my self-identification with Rod Taylor. He was the kind of man I aspired to be and, in many ways, became.** **Hitchcock wanted an actor with ‚Äúballs‚Äù. No Jimmy Stewart or Cary Grant would do. And, most of all, he wanted an actor with the physical presence and the acting ability to make the terror real and make us believe the danger. And Rod was all of that.** **But as I‚Äôve also written, *‚ÄúNever confuse the actor with the role‚Äù. *I had several opportunities to meet Rod and decided against. Rod Taylor was too important to me to take the chance of not liking him.** **There have been countless reviews and analyses of ‚ÄúThe Birds‚Äù over the last half-century, the technical marvel that it was given the film-making limitations of the time. But at its core, it has always been a character-study, an exploration of how ordinary people behave under extraordinary circumstances ‚Äì when nature turns against us ‚Äì and why the film resonates more powerfully today than it did sixty years ago.** **‚ÄúThe Birds‚Äù has to be one of the most analyzed and debated films ever made because of its intentional ambiguity, the fact that the bird attacks are never explained. Hitchcock was determined it not be considered ‚Äòscience fiction‚Äô, allowing for a wide range of interpretations. Some critics have claimed that it‚Äôs the characters who are the real ‚Äòbirds‚Äô, pecking and clawing at each other.** **What begins as an almost romantic comedy meeting in a bird shop, soon turns almost obsessive as Melanie (Tippi Hedren) seeks out Mitch (Rod Taylor) at his remote weekend family home, beautiful yet vaguely ominous Bodega Bay, and confronts his very needy mother Lydia (Jessica Tandy) and his old flame Annie (Suzanne Pleshette).** **And as the various relationships and conflicts unfold, suspense slowly builds in a series of escalating, inexplicable bird attacks builds to an all-out assault on the town and on the impromptu family unit boarded up inside the house as wave after wave challenges any illusion of safety.** **Several years ago, I wrote some commentary for Diane Tomasik‚Äôs excellent ‚ÄòThe Complete Rod Taylor Site‚Äô:** ***"The story may seem to be about Melanie Daniels, but it all depends upon Mitch Brenner."*** ***‚ÄúRod is the center of gravity for the entire film. His performance strikes just the right balance of strength and inner conflict. Too much of one or the other and the whole picture falls apart. His reactions to the birds are what make the terror real and allow us to share it.‚Äù***

text: STATEMENT OF SPEAKER FERDINAND MARTIN ROMUALDEZ ON THE ISRAEL-HAMAS CONFLICT Today, I join voices from around the world in strongly condemning the heartbreaking attacks against innocent civilians in Israel. The devastation and loss suffered by families during such significant moments of reverence are beyond words. It is a reminder that the path of violence only deepens wounds and rifts. I urge all involved parties, especially the militant rulers of Hamas, to pave a way toward a peaceful resolution. The history of this region has seen enough bloodshed; sustainable peace is the only way forward. To our Filipino brothers and sisters living or working in Israel, my thoughts are with you. The Departments of Foreign Affairs (DFA) and Migrant Workers (DMW), and Overseas Workers Welfare Administration (OWWA) are now working overtime to ensure your safety and well-being. Please remain vigilant and prioritize your safety during these turbulent times. Your welfare is a matter of paramount importance to us. I align myself with the sentiments of global leaders and advocates for peace, emphasizing that dialogue and understanding are paramount. True change can only be achieved when we respect and protect the rights of civilians, as stipulated under international law. May peace prevail in the region and may the global community come together to support a harmonious resolution to this longstanding conflict. #19thCongress #HouseOfRepsPH #AgendaForProsperity #LiderNgKongreso

TEAMSTERS KICK OFF UNITY 2023 CONFERENCE IN BOSTON Hundreds of Teamsters gathered this morning in Boston to kick off the 2023 Unity Conference. Tom Mari, President of Teamsters Boston Local 25 and Secretary-Treasurer of Joint Council 10, opened today's General Session by welcoming Teamster members and leaders from all over North America to the city of Boston. Conference attendees heard from General President Sean M. O'Brien and General Secretary-Treasurer Fred Zuckerman along with Representative Stephen F. Lynch, ITF - International Transport Workers' Federation General Secretary Steve Cotton, and Massachusetts Governor Maura Healey. "We couldn't have won the contract we did at UPS without unity," O'Brien said. "Moving forward, we have to be united to take on the corporate bullies at UPS, Amazon, Delta, Anheuser-Busch, and others. The fight at UPS is never over. We are just getting started. Enforcing this contract at UPS is going to be key to organizing at Amazon." "We are in a historic moment with strikes across the labor movement. The days of avoiding conflict are over. We have to take on these challenges head-on," O'Brien added. "We need to organize in our core industries and negotiate the best contracts for our members," Zuckerman said. "That's what Sean and I have been focused on since we took office. We have good political leaders who have our backs and we need more of them. If politicians aren't with us and all working Americans, we vote them out. It's not complicated." "Twenty million transportation workers around the world know the Teamsters...The world stopped during the pandemic. Transportation workers didn't. We have to strive to improve workers' lives, but that's only possible with strong leadership and support from the rank-and-file," Cotton said. "I am proud to be here standing alongside Sean O‚ÄôBrien, a leader from Massachusetts who now leads the national fight for the Teamsters. Sean never gives up fighting for working families. He's not afraid to be the underdog. We've been working together to take on bad corporate actors," Gov. Healey said. The General Session continues this morning with more speakers. Stay tuned.

1908 Gustav Adolph Mossa : : Sapho. Mossa (1883 ‚Äì 1971) is considered today as the last French symbolist painter. His work, already recognized before the First World War, was then deliberately obscured by the artist himself. He lived all his life in Nice and devoted himself mainly to his role as curator of the city's Museum of Fine Arts, a position he took over from his father, the founding curator of this museum. His symbolist and sulphurous work was hidden, then rediscovered in the reserves after his death in 1971. Like Gustave Moreau, his symbolist work is haunted by references to literature. But unlike his contemporaries, Mossa innovates by placing these figures in his century, the Belle Epoque. In the meticulous details of his works, he develops a rich iconography of Art Nouveau: furniture, costumes, jewelry. Many aspects of Mossa's paintings of this period were also indictive of the decadent movement, with his references to Diabolism, depictions of lesbianism (such as his two paintings of Sappho),or an emphasis on violent, sadistic or morbid scenes. Women are omnipresent in his work, under the guise of the femme fatale, even phallic and castrating; she is angel and demon at the same time. Through his work, Mossa explores his own unconscious and depicts the perpetual conflict of life and death drives: Eros and Thanatos. Like F√©licien Rops, many of Mossa's works still appear provocative today.

(SPOILER ALERT for Kingdom of Ruins EP 1) First impressions of EP 1 were just fantastic! A very strong and depressing (in a good way) start to a very promising series. The world building is great I my opinion. I loved how they mixed in magic with science and technology to create conflict between the human race and the witch race (the 'Gear Expansion Revolution' sounds very strikingly similar to our real world's "Industrial Revolution") with loads of depth (it's not all for backdrop which I love a lot here). Seeing modern buildings alongside medieval style structures was bizarre yet very cool in this regard. I love the factor that despite the revolution bringing some form of "peace" and "prosperity" to the world, human beings still wage war, terror, slavery and other horrible things on each other. That's human nature which no matter how many innovations in humankind's history, will never disappear so I like they included this realistic factor here. The plot and characters also started off very strong. Chloe and Adolis, despite appearing together with limited screen time were lovable to the very end. Chloe's death was horrific (kind of reminds of how in WW2, the Axis powers of Japan and Germany would kill off people of other races they deemed 'inferior' to them) and our girl didn't deserve to go out like that üò≠. The plot is sounding strikingly similar to "Akame Ga Kill" which is not a bad thing but I hope this one turns out more unique and fleshed out (and no, I don't have a problem with Adolis laying the entire Redia Empire to ruins alongside that trash of a 'king' and it's awful inhabitants). Lastly, the animation, visuals and sound design were all great throughout the episode. The voice acting was superb as well (specially when Adolis was in pain from disbelief seeing that happened to Chloe Infront of him). I hope this series continues being this strong in future episodes. So far, it has been a great beginning.

Occasionally people ask, ‚Äòhow can I let my child go to a parent who isn‚Äôt this, and does that, and it won‚Äôt be good for them ‚Ä¶.?‚Äô It‚Äôs the nightmare situation an alienated parent finds themselves in. Pressure is put on the child to leave, reject and ultimately be alienated from a parent they love and who loves them. How can we let them go? The story of Solomon describes how the loving parent lets go. I‚Äôve done many posts on letting go as it can be hard to understand, especially for others, and family courts. Why don‚Äôt we fight more? We do as much as we can. But there comes a time when it only harms the child more, so we let go. With love. It is our sacrifice because we love them. In the story of the two mothers in Kings (3:16-28), two women living in the same house gave birth to babies at the same time. One mother rolled over on her baby, smothering him, and he died. She swapped out babies and tried to convince her friend that the dead baby was hers. The true mother took the dispute to King Solomon who discovered the truth. The true mother was the one who wouldn‚Äôt agree to the baby being cut in half by sword. The alienating parent doesn‚Äôt care what harm they do, they thrive on conflict. We want what is best for our children. They want what is best for them. If only our family courts were as wise as Solomon. I‚Äôm not suggesting the sword test. But there should be many ways they can identify the loving parent from the alienating, manipulative, selfish and abusive parent. The loving parent wants the child to have more family, not less, and more love, not less. #TheThing is a 1982 American science fiction horror film directed by John Carpenter and written by Bill Lancaster. Based on the 1938 John W. Campbell Jr. novella Who Goes There?, it tells the story of a group of American researchers in Antarctica who encounter the eponymous "Thing", a parasitic extraterrestrial life-form that assimilates, then imitates other organisms. The group is overcome by paranoia and conflict as they learn that they can no longer trust each other and that any one of them could be the Thing. The film stars Kurt Russell as the team's helicopter pilot, R.J. MacReady, and features A. Wilford Brimley, T. K. Carter, David Clennon, Keith David, Richard Dysart, Charles Hallahan, Peter Maloney, Richard Masur, Donald Moffat, Joel Polis, and Thomas G. Waites in supporting roles. The Thing A human silhouette wearing a thick coat and hood stands against a white background. Beams of white emanate from the hood opening, obscuring its identity. Our Lady of the Most Holy Rosary Feast: October 7 This feast was established by Pope St. Pius V in thanksgiving for the victory at Lepanto, 7 Oct 1571, which stopped the Turkish invasion of Europe. Importance: The word Rosary means ‚ÄúCrown of Roses,‚Äù and each prayer in the Rosary is considered a flower presented to Mary. It is called the ‚ÄúBreviary of the Common People‚Äù and the ‚ÄúPsalms of the Illiterate.‚Äù The prayers we repeat are Biblical and hence ‚Äúinspired,‚Äù and the mysteries we meditate upon are taken from the lives of Jesus and Mary. The ‚ÄúOur Father‚Äù is a prayer taught by Jesus Himself. The ‚ÄúHail Mary‚Äù is also rooted in the Scriptures. Its first half echoes the words of the Archangel Gabriel and those of Elizabeth, both addressed to Mary. The rest of our petition , ‚Äúpray for us, sinners, now and at the hour of our death‚Äù is added by the Church, seeking Mary‚Äôs intercession. The third prayer ‚Äî the ‚ÄúGlory be to the Father‚Äù ‚Äî ancient in its wording, surely reflects the unceasing prayer of adoration and praise found in the Book of Revelation. The various events in the lives of Jesus and Mary on which we meditate during the Rosary are expressions of the Paschal Mystery, that is, the Life, Death and Resurrection of Jesus, in which Mary shared. History: Prayer using rosary beads is as old as mankind. The Hindus in India used to recite the thousand names of their gods and goddesses and their ‚Äúmantra‚Äù prayers using multi-beaded rosaries, and their sages wear such rosaries around the neck, constantly rolling the beads in prayer. The Jews used beads to repeat the psalms, the Laws of Moses and the memorized sayings of the prophets. The Muslims use rosaries with a hundred beads for their prayer. In the ninth century, the Christian monks who recited the 150 psalms instructed the illiterate common people to recite the Our Father 150 times. It was in the eleventh century that the Europeans added the Hail Mary to the Our Father. In 1214, according to the legend, the Blessed Virgin Mary appeared to St. Dominic Guzman and instructed him to pray the Rosary in a new form as an effective antidote against the Albigensian heresy. The Rosary devotion attained its present form around 1500 A.D. An additional boost to the Rosary devotion was given in 1917, when our Blessed Mother, in her sixth apparition to the three shepherd children, on the thirteenth of May, asked them to, ‚ÄúSay the Rosary every day‚Ä¶ Pray, pray a lot and offer sacrifices for sinners‚Ä¶ I am Our Lady of the Rosary.‚Äù The ‚ÄúFatima prayer‚Äù (O my Jesus forgive us our sins, save us from the fires of Hell and bring all souls to Heaven, expecially those who are most in need of Your mercy), requested by Mary herself at Fatima (July 13, 1917), was added following the ‚ÄúGlory be‚Ä¶‚Äùn after the 1930 acceptance of the Bishop of the apparitions as genuine century. Pope St. John Paul II enriched the Rosary by adding the ‚ÄúLuminous Mysteries‚Äù Introductory Prayer to the Rosary - Saint Louis de Montfort (Sign of the Cross Prayer) I unite with all the Angels and Saints in Heaven, with all the just on earth, and with all the faithful here present. I unite with Thee, O my Jesus, in order to praise worthily Thy holy Mother, and to praise Thee in her and through her. I renounce all the distractions that I may have during this Rosary, which I wish to say with modesty, attention, and devotion, just as if it were to be the last of my life. We offer Thee, O most Holy Trinity, this Creed in honor of all the mysteries of our Faith; this Our Father, and these three Hail Marys in honor of the unity of Thy Essence and the Trinity of Thy Persons. We ask of Thee a lively faith, a firm hope, and an ardent charity. Amen. (I Believe‚Ä¶Our Father‚Ä¶ three Hail Marys) To the Queen of the Most Holy Rosary Queen of the most holy Rosary, in these times of such brazen impiety, manifest thy power with the signs of thine ancient victories, and from thy throne, whence thou dost dispense pardon and graces, mercifully regard the Church of thy Son, His Vicar on earth, and every order of clergy and laity, who are sore oppressed in the mighty conflict. Do thou, who art the powerful vanquisher of all heresies, hasten the hour of mercy, even though the hour of God's justice is every day provoked by the countless sins of men. For me who am the least of men, kneeling before thee in supplication, do thou obtain the grace I need to live righteously upon earth and to reign among the just in heaven, the while in company with all faithful Christians throughout the world, I salute thee and acclaim thee as Queen of the most holy Rosary. Queen of the most holy Rosary, pray for us!

Noratus Cemetery, Armenia. Noratus cemetery is situated in the province of Gexarkunik, near the village of Noratus in Armenia. The site has been occupied since the Bronze Age, as attested by the megalithic fort near the village and other artefacts dating to the Bronze and Iron Age. The present-day village was founded in 1829. The cemetery of Noratus is the largest in the territory of Armenia after the cemetery of Julfa in the Nakhichevan Province that was destroyed between 1998 and 2006 during a conflict with a neighboring country. The cemetery has been used from as early as the Early Christian period up to the modern day, as is indicated by the remains the funerary stelae dating back to the sixth or seventh century, and tomb-stones of a more recent date. The cemetery of Noratus has a unique, extraordinary collection of khatchkars, containing more than 900 pieces from the ninth or tenth to the eighteenth centuries; the majority of the khatchkars were erected between the thirteenth and seventeenth centuries. This type of cemetery is also called a ‚Äúkhatchkar-forest‚Äù. Most of the khatchkars are grouped, indicating the burial place of different families. There are also tiny graves or rectangular mausoleums carrying cross stones. Some of the khatchkars stand on pedestals, with some among them reaching a height of 1.5m. Many khatchkars were carved during the revival of the khatchkar tradition in the sixteenth and seventeenth centuries, bearing witness to oriental influences widespread in Armenian art during the rule of the Safavid Dynasty in Persia. Several tombstones in the cemetery depict carved scenes of banqueting and hunting. These could indicate the royal or noble affiliation of the owner or owners.

text: Thank you to everyone who contributed to our 2023 Discovery Drive! As many of you may know, one of our biggest funding projects going on right now is our new bear den and habitat space. This additional area will increase our capacity for housing bears that are removed from the wild due to human conflict, and provide many new enrichment opportunities. With the funds raised, we have been able to make steady construction progress this season- most recently a convoy of 14 cement trucks helped us lay down the den roof/ base of the upper habitat. The funding from our annual appeal also helps us purchase food and enrichment for the animals, including live fish and materials to make things like a new firehose raft for the otters! We love having new and exciting ways to change up the daily routine of the animals. Pictured: 1 and 2: Ongoing construction to our new Bear Den building. 2. Male river otters Cliff and Wade checking out their firehose raft 3. Male river otter Wade searching around on a log for food items

BREAKING: FG calls for de-escalation of hostilities between Israel, Palestine The federal government of Nigeria has called for a de-escalation of the latest crisis between Israel and the Palestinian Hamas militant group. In a statement signed by Yusuf Tuggar, minister of foreign affairs, the federal government called on both sides to exercise restraint and prioritise the safety of civilians. In the early hours of Saturday, the Hamas militant group infiltrated Israel from the Gaza strip, in what has been described as an unprecedented attack. Benjamin Netanyahu, Israeli prime minister, has since called the invasion an act of war. The Israeli death toll from the crisis has surpassed 100, per latest reports, with more than 200 killed in Israeli reprisal attacks in Gaza. ‚ÄúThe federal government of Nigeria is deeply concerned about the outbreak of hostilities between Israel and Hamas in the early hours of Saturday, 7th October, 2023 and calls for de-escalation and ceasefire,‚Äù the statement reads. ‚ÄúThe cycle of violence and retaliation that the current escalation has assumed, only serves to perpetuate an unending cycle of pain and suffering for the civilian population that bear the brunt of every conflict. ‚ÄúWe are therefore calling for a peaceful resolution of the conflict through dialogue.‚Äù #israelpalestinewar

At the time of writing (October 2023), this ongoing conflict has led to an estimated death toll of at least 4.5 million, according to researchers at Brown University. Dhuoda: A 9th-Century Woman Who Wrote a Book: "Liber Manualis" or "Handbook" for her son William. One of the most fascinating documents of the early Middle Ages must be the book that Dhuoda (pronounced Doda), a Frankish noblewoman, wrote for her son, William; it was written between November 841 and February, 843. When Dhuoda started the book, William, who was then aged fourteen, had been given as a hostage by his father, Bernard of Septimania, to the eighteen-year-old Charles the Bald, after the Battle of Fontenoy in May 841. Dhuoda composed the Handbook so that William could carry and hold it in his hand, a manual in other words. The object of her book was to offer a mother‚Äôs advice to her son on how to survive in a dangerous world and to remind him of his duties both to his father, and to his king, and on his behaviour as a chaste Christian warrior. The background was the unsettled era when the Carolingian Empire was breaking up and the sons of Louis the Pious fought each other over their share of their father‚Äôs empire, bringing devastation and ruin to many in its wake. In common with so many people of the early Middle Ages, almost nothing is known of Dhuoda‚Äôs parentage or background, other than what can be gleaned from her book, though she does not mention her own family of origin at all. However, she tells us that ‚ÄúI was given in lawful marriage on 29th June, 824, to my Lord Bernard‚Äù[i] in the Imperial Chapel in Aachen. Given the status of the man she married Dhuoda herself would have come from one of the noble families of the Carolingian empire and I have seen a suggestion that her father may have been Sancho, Duke of Gascony, though this is speculation. Bernard of Septimania, Dhuoda‚Äôs husband, was a second cousin of Louis the Pious, both were great-grandsons of Charles Martel as Louis‚Äôs grandfather Pippin the Short was a brother of Aldana, Bernard‚Äôs grandmother. Bernard‚Äôs father was William of Gellone or William of Aquitaine, a saint since 1066, and a prominent character in the book ‚ÄúHoly Blood Holy Grail‚Äù. In 826 Bernard and Dhuoda took up residence in Uz√®s, now in the Gard d√©partement, in Southern France, but then one of the major towns of Septimania, on the Spanish Marches. This coincided with Bernard‚Äôs appointment as Count of Barcelona, by Louis the Pious. Dhuoda and Bernard's son William was born on 29th November 826. By 829 it is known that Bernard was at the Court in Aachen, as he had been appointed Chamberlain by Louis the Pious that year. Bernard was one of the most controversial members of the Imperial Court, his position as chamberlain brought him into more or less daily contact with the Empress Judith with whom he was accused of committing adultery and of engaging in magical practices. In 830 he was deprived of some of his counties and also of his office as Chamberlain. In 834, during the rebellion of Lothar, the eldest son of Louis the Pious, against his father, Bernard‚Äôs sister Gerberga, a nun, became a casualty of the conflict. Gerberga was captured by Lothar who accused her of plotting with Judith and Bernard and of engaging in magical practices with them. The chronicler, Thegan, Bishop of Trier tells us that ‚ÄúLothar tortured her for a long time‚Äù [ii] and the Annals of St Bertin tell us that ‚ÄúBernard‚Äôs sister was put in a barrel and drowned in the Sa√¥ne‚Äù like a witch [iii]. This execution of Bernard‚Äôs sister, Gerberga, obviously made a strong impression at the time as it is mentioned by most of the chroniclers of the era. Dhuoda had remained behind in Uz√®s since the birth of William but how long he stayed with her is not clear; he may have been brought up in the household of one of his father‚Äôs brothers, or even in the court at Aachen. That being alone and responsible for Uz√®s was not easy is made clear by Dhuoda in this passage from the Handbook: ‚ÄúI acknowledge that, to defend the interests of my lord and master Bernard, and so that my service to him might not weaken in the March and elsewhere --so that he not abandon you and me, as some men do--I know that I have gone greatly into debt. To respond to great necessities, I have frequently borrowed great sums, not only from Christians but also from Jews. To the extent that I have been able, I have repaid them. To the extent that I can in the future, I will always do so.‚Äù That Bernard returned to Dhuoda at least once is known as her second son was born on 22nd March 841. However, ‚ÄúThis child‚Ä¶ was still tiny and had not yet received the grace of baptism when Bernard, my lord and the father of you both, had the baby brought to him in Aquitaine in the company of Elefantus, Bishop of Uz√®s‚Ä¶.‚Äù And ‚ÄúAs for you, I have heard that your father, Bernard, has given you as a hostage to the lord king Charles‚Ä¶..‚Äù - following the Battle of Fontenoy in June 841. Dhuoda exhorts William to care for ‚Äúyour little brother, whose name I still do not know‚Ä¶..when the time has come that he has learned to speak and to read, show him this little volume (truncated)

ARGUMENT TURNS DEADLY AFTER A MAN IS SHOT AND KILLED AT A FERGUSON QUIKTRIP Yesterday we received a call at 1:28 am regarding heavy police presence 10700 block of West Florissant. According to authorities a verbal disagreement between a security guard and an unidentified male escalated into gunshots being exchanged. The situation started from the now deceased male having a minor conflict with the cashier on duty about not having the proper identification to purchase tobacco products. He would return shortly and get into a verbal altercation with the armed security guard. Allegedly he pulled out a firearm and the two began to exchange gunfire. The security guard would fatally shoot and kill him. This shooting makes the second death at a QuikTrip gas station within a week in St. Louis County.

No matter how spiritually ‚Äúwoke‚Äù we may think we are, we still have deeper issues which can only be worked out within the context of relationship. Left alone, we settle into comfortable patterns that limit the range of our emotional awareness and personal expression. However, once we step out of our comfort zone and open up to others, previously unnoticed/denied aspects of ourselves begin to emerge. At first, they make waves in the calm waters of our hearts, evoking passion and excitement. But when we let them in deeply enough, it‚Äôs like stirring up a pool of still water - all the heavy and messy things which settled at the bottom of our awareness are forced to emerge to the surface. When our otherwise hard-to-reach issues get stirred up for us to look at, we have an opportunity to embrace these fragmented parts of ourselves, to become more integrated and whole. This is a blessing in disguise, albeit a challenging one. Intimate relationships demand a depth of intensity and vulnerability which is the fuel for both transcendent passion and crippling conflict. This is why many esoteric teachings point to the ‚Äúpolar couple/ twin flame‚Äù archetype as the most powerful of alchemical unions. Intimate relationships have the potential for astoundingly accelerated transformation. Whether that transformation leads to conscious evolution or unconscious sabotage depends entirely on each person‚Äôs individual state of Being. If you and your partner aren‚Äôt engaged in sincere, deep, holistic self-work, there can only be 2 outcomes for this kind of relationship. Either you and your partner will settle into a relatively comfortable but very limited relationship of matrix-based pleasures and pursuits where your dysfunctions harmonize, but leave little room for expansion of the soul‚Ä¶ OR‚Ä¶ the relationship will dissolve to make way for something greater in your life. This is the case with the vast majority of relationships in the world, which is why people are often so dissatisfied in relationships. However, if you and your partner are committed to nurture the healing alchemical fire within each other, the richness of this kind of relationship is extraordinary! ~Rebel Lion Artist: Unknown

HOLY AND DIVINE LOVE MESSAGES FROM THE PAST
(for us to reflect on today - October 6, 2023) 

April 19, 2009 
Heaven Speaks to the Heart of the World 
(specifically - the path the world is taking) 

Midnight Service at the United Hearts Field - Feast of Divine Mercy 

(This message was given in multiple parts over several days.) 

Jesus is here as He is in the Divine Mercy Image; there is a huge Flame behind Him. He says: "I am your Jesus, born Incarnate. I come to you tonight from the Will of the Eternal Father Whose Flame of Love you see behind Me." 

"My brothers and sisters, I come to you as your Merciful Jesus. Those who love Me understand My Mercy and My Love, which are one. These are the ones that allow My Mercy and My Love to shine through them into the world. These are the ones who understand the call of My Heart to repentance of each soul. I will refuse no one who turns to Me with a repentant heart." 

"Today the foundation of a one-world government has been laid through the global economic collapse which Satan has orchestrated. As this unfolds, remember that your free will remains intact. No one can dictate the affections of your heart. Live always in Holy Love. Remain calm; be at peace. If your heart is steeped in love of God and love of neighbor, you are safe, for I am with you." 

"Hope, indeed, springs eternal for those who place their trust in Me. See in all world events the coming of the Kingdom of the Divine Will of My Father. Believe in this Kingdom - the New Jerusalem - which is alive in hearts living in Holy Love." 

"Those who have made hatred into a 'religion' will destroy themselves. They cannot succeed, for Truth will be victorious. Holy Love is the Heart of Truth. In truth I tell you, it is now the hour of decision. Take up the weapons of prayer and sacrifice as I call together My army ** against evil. My victims of love are the officers in this spiritual army. I tell you, the battle against evil must be won in hearts before it is won in the world." 

"During these decisive and difficult times, it is important to realize that conflict and wars arise in hearts because of conflict with the Commandments of Love. God desires all of creation to be in harmony with His Divine Will. This is why He has created this apparition site and this Mission. The more that people accept and surrender to Holy Love, * the greater the graces poured out here. Therefore, with hearts that emulate Divine Mercy and Divine Love, make the Messages known." 

"My Mercy will never be depleted, but the dawn of My Divine Justice is at hand. Satan seeks to destroy all that is good and loving, using people and nature to accomplish his goals. Depend on Divine Mercy and Divine Love to see you through the worst of times. From My Love and My Mercy flows My Provision." 

"I invite you to realize that when the Holy Love in your heart is compromised, every virtue begins to erode. It is as if the roots of a great tree were Holy Love. The trunk would be humility; the blossoms on this great tree are the different virtues. The roots and the trunk (love and humility) must remain healthy for the whole tree to be healthy. In the spiritual life, Holy Love and Holy Humility feed and support all the other virtues. Therefore, if Holy Love erodes, faith and hope are weakened. If humility is compromised, the rest of the tree of virtues begins to wither." 

"Within each soul is this mystical tree of virtue; it gives life or else it withers and dies. In society this tree of virtue is necessary towards world peace. If it is ignored and not watered with Holy Trust, the world around the tree suffers. This is what leads to lack of peace in hearts." 

"You may wonder at My depiction of personal holiness as this tree of virtue. But I invite you to see that each soul's journey or growth in holiness affects the heart of the world, for the heart of the world is a composite of the hearts of all its citizenry. The tree of virtue in the heart of the world is drying up from lack of care. In its place is the tree of antipathy towards God and His Commandments. The roots of this tree are hatred; the trunk is arrogant pride; the blossoms are not blooms but rather spoiled fruit - each one opposing virtue. This tree is beginning to thrive, nourished by man's over-indulgent trust in himself - through self-love." 

"With a compassionate heart for the spiritual crisis in the heart of the world, realize that the tree of virtue stretches heavenward towards perfection in God's Will. On the other hand, the tree of antipathy towards God suffers from neglect and lack of care and takes on a countenance of death. Unless the gardener notices this poor tree, it will face a grim future." 

"This is why I have come here - to draw attention to the state of the heart of the world. My plea is urgent. Nourish your hearts with the food of virtue. Do not be motivated by self-love, but by love of God and neighbor. This is what will redirect the future of the world. (truncated)

UPDATE: Kenya's President, William Ruto stand on the Israel-Palestine War.üëáüëá Kenya joins the rest of the world in solidarity with the State of Israel and unequivocally condemn terrorism and attacks on innocent civilians in the country. The people of Kenya and their government hereby express deepest sympathy and send condolences to the families of all victims. We also wish a speedy recovery to the injured. Kenya strongly maintains that there exists no justification whatsoever for terrorism, which constitutes a serious threat to international peace and security. All acts of terrorism and violent extremism are abhorrent, criminal and unjustifiable, regardless of the perpetrator, or their motivations. The international community must mobilise to bring the perpetrators, organizers, financiers, sponsors, supporters and enablers of these reprehensible criminal acts of terrorism to account and speedily bring them to justice. In consideration of the complex and delicate context of the security situation in Israel-Palestine, Kenya also makes a call for the de-escalation of violence and urges all parties to restrain from further military action, given its potential to intensify carnage and the suffering of innocent civilians, and to trigger heightened tension in the region and beyond. We are profoundly disturbed that civilians continue to be intentionally targeted in this conflict, as a consequence of which the number of casualties continues to rise. We therefore call on all parties to respect the rights of civilians and honour their obligations under international law. Finally, we take this opportunity to reiterate our firm stand in solidarity with all those calling on the parties to desist from further attacks, promptly effect cease-fire and embark on a path towards a peaceful resolution of the conflict.

CMJ Friends & Supporters: We are asking that you stand with us in prayer! This weekend should have marked the launch of our end of year fundraising campaign. However, in light of what is happening in Israel, we are setting that aside, and asking for intercession for the Land of Israel. You may already have read news feeds announcing rocket fire and military skirmishes in Israel between Hamas soldiers, local police, and the Israel Defense Force. It is impossible to determine at this time how serious or prolonged this season of conflict will be. As you are probably aware, this is different from past rounds of the conflict in that the terrorists from Gaza have infiltrated Israeli towns and settlements in the south. This time as far as we can tell, the region stands at a watershed moment. We will issue regular prayer alerts as new needs become clear. A leading newspaper in Israel published the following, only minutes ago: There have been terrible massacres in some communities and military bases. Although thousands of rockets and missiles have been fired into Israel, from the south to Jerusalem and the greater Tel Aviv area, that has been mainly a diversion: Hamas' military effort is concentrated on the Israeli communities on the Gaza border. Tragically, it has been very successful. First, a couple of reminders. Nothing occurs outside the providence of the Father. So pray in hope for all of His disciples here in Israel and Gaza. Be aware that these troubles are accompanied by digital misinformation. So, caution is required. As of the sending of this email, the situation on the ground is as follows: 1. Rocket fire continues to land in Israel. Over 3000 rockets have been fired in the last ten hours. 2. There are over 1000 wounded and over 100 dead. The likely number could be hundreds more. 3. Israeli security services report that there are still 20 locations of ongoing fighting with Hamas militants within Israeli territory. 4. The IDF has confirmed that hostages have been taken. Numbers are unconfirmed but could be between dozens to over a hundred. Key things to pray for right now are: 1. For all those who have been injured by rocket fire or terrorist gunfire. 2. For those who have been kidnapped 3. That the officials in Israel who will decide how to respond, will be graced with the wisdom of the Lord whether or not they ask for it. 4. For the perseverance and calm of our staff as we serve our guests and pilgrims who are often quite frightened. For their safe passage home and for local people who may be needing help as well. 5. Pray for the upcoming groups scheduled to come - for wisdom in how to proceed. 6. That the Lord gives our leadership wisdom in the decisions we will need to make in the coming days. 7. Especially intercede for members of our staff, young men from our communities who are part of response teams serving as soldiers or medics in harm‚Äôs way. Pray for members of our congregations that have either been called up themselves or have children and grandchildren that are serving in the military and emergency services. 8. Pray for the residents of Gaza. Through our online ministry in Arabic, we are getting messages from people that we are working with and discipling who are frightened and equally fearful for their lives. There is much for which to pray. However, above all, please pray for God's sovereignty in these difficult times. May His kingdom come, and may His will be done. Thank you for your partnership of prayer in our calling. - CMJ Israel Staff If you want to know how you can either pray and help further, please email us at office@cmj-israel.org

THE THIRD WAY, OR HOW NOT TO CHOOSE SIDES IN A WAR When I wake up in the morning and hear about the attack on Israel from Gaza, I enter into a whirlwind of emotions. Feelings of rage, anger, sadness, judgement, failure, despair all come to the surface and get entangled into a knot in my stomach. The best - and the easiest, I guess - is to detach, like most westerners do. ‚ÄòOh, another fight between Israel and Hamas.‚Äô But I can‚Äôt. I‚Äôm too much involved. And I don‚Äôt even understand why. ‚ÄòWhat do I have to do with this whole mess?‚Äô I ask myself in a failed attempt to escape the misery. But fate looks at me with a grim smile on its face. There is no escape, no way out. Just like there is no way out for the people of Israel and the people of Palestine. The poisonous cup must be emptied to the bottom. I think about the ‚ÄòMeditation for Peace‚Äô we did last week, during a gathering of Israeli Women Wage Peace and the Palestinian Women of the Sun. As a group of internationals we visualized us standing in a circle around them, not taking sides, just holding space. How must they feel now, after what happened? Who wants to be seen with the enemy these days? At best people will think of them as naive, at worst as being traitors to their own people. I also think about the friends I know on both sides: in Jerusalem, Tel Aviv, Gaza and kibbutz Be‚Äôeri, close to the Gaza border. They must be in a terrible place, with so much fear and sadness and hatred going on. They probably go through the same rollercoaster as I experience, or even worse. I even wonder if they are still alive. Only when listening to some beautiful music I start to cry and let my grief out. I get in touch with all the pain and suffering, including my own. Afterwards I feel more relieved. Underneath the sadness I have a deeper realization: Yes, I am involved, and I have to take my place, even if I‚Äôm an outsider, even if I am scared, even if I make mistakes. Because when I read the different newssites I only read opinions and quotes of leaders that make everything worse then it already is. Everyone seems the need to take sides, to judge - just like I did - to blame, to become angry, to become enraged and to add to the split that is already there. The attack on Israel ignites a worldwide indignation in most western countries. ‚ÄòIsrael has the right to defend itself against terrorists,‚Äô all political leaders sing in choir. But during the many attacks on the Westbank and Gaza over the last few months there was the same indignation in Muslim countries: why is nobody calling justice for the people being killed or chased by settlers or the Israeli raids?‚Äô they say. We are all swept away in a tsunami of ‚Äòus versus them‚Äô, of right versus wrong, of the good guys versus the bad guys. How can we stay in the middle of the hurricane of emotions and not be caught in the merry-go-round of action and reaction, of victims and perpetrators, of anger and blame, of killing and revenge? How to not choose sides in a war? And yet, how to speak your truth and bring clarity in a conflict that seems to be the conflict of all conflicts, the war of all wars? ‚ÄòIf there is peace in Jerusalem, there will be peace in the world.‚Äô But up till now it is just a bloody mess that is only getting worse. So how to get out of the quackmire? What helps us in a conflict that seems endless and hopeless? Are there any guidelines that can give us directions? In the last 20 years that I got involved in this story and gave many workshops of traumahealing to both Israelians and Palestinians - I learned a couple of things which I would like to bring to the table, in an effort to bring some clarity. 1. There are two ways out of pain: one is to blame others, to fight, to inflict pain on someone else, to judge, to start a war and kill the one that seems the cause of your pain. The other way is to go inside, to feel the pain, to cry and grief, and to learn to stay with it. The way out versus the way in. The first leads to more pain, more hatred, more duality, more chaos; the second leads to integration, wisdom, healing, and compassion. The first way is the most easy, the second way is the road less traveled, and definitely harder to choose. 2. Where women will sooner tend to choose the second way, men mostly choose the first way out: sadly but true, it is the mostly men who wage war, build walls, fight the enemy and ready to kill the ‚Äòother‚Äô. We, as men, haven‚Äôt learned the inner path; the path of grieving, crying, holding space, embracing, connecting and healing. It is being deemed unmanly, soft, feminine, weak. We need to be strong, powerful, the winner, the protector. It is probably this false image of masculinity that keeps us being trapped in the endless cycle of violence. It is no coincidence that the group of women that wants to stop the war are called ‚ÄòWomen Wage Peace.‚Äô Because Men Wage War. 3. If masculinity is part of the problem, then it is also part of the solution. For men it is difficult (truncated)

Media Statement 07 October 2023. South Africa calls for the immediate cessation of violence, restraint, and peace between Israel and Palestine South Africa expresses its grave concern over the recent devastating escalation in the Israeli-Palestinian conflict. The new conflagration has arisen from the continued illegal occupation of Palestine land, continued settlement expansion, desecration of the Al Aqsa mosque and Christian holy sites, and ongoing oppression of the Palestinian people. The region is in desperate need of a credible peace process that delivers on the calls of a plethora of previous UN resolutions for a two-state solution and a just and comprehensive peace between Israel and Palestine. South Africa, working together with the international community, seeks to ensure a lasting and durable peace that produces a viable, contiguous Palestinian State, existing side-by-side in peace with Israel, within the 1967 internationally recognised borders, with East Jerusalem as its capital. UN resolutions and international law matter. The international community can not avoid its duty to act, and together, we must shoulder the responsibility to remove obstacles to peace and any violations of international law. Violence, killings, imprisonment, forced removals, illegal settlements, and the continued siege of Gaza are not conducive to resolving the conflict. Urgent attention must be given to resolving the final status issues such as borders, the status of Jerusalem, the release of political prisoners, and the right of return. No real and lasting peace in Israel, Palestine, and the region is possible in the absence of a just and comprehensive resolution of the conflict. Israelis, Palestinians, and the region do not stand to gain anything from escalated tensions, increased violence, growing instability, and a continued and protracted violent conflict. South Africa therefore calls on all sides to seize the opportunity for peace as opposed to violence, and for the international community to actively rise on the side of its own International resolutions and establish a credible peace process. South Africa stands ready to share its experience in mediation and conflict resolution as it has done on the continent and around the world. Issued by DIRCO

What's for breakfast today? Do a fact check of your diet and lifestyle. Non communicable diseases in Malaysia is so high. 1 in 5 live with diabetes, 1 in 3 with hypertension, and 50% are obese. Chronic kidney disease is at almost 16%. In Malaysia, more than two out of 10 children below five years of age are stunted (short). At 21.8%, Malaysia's child stunting rate is higher than in lower middle-income countries like Ghana (17.5%) and even conflict-ridden areas such as Palestine (7.4%) and Iraq (12.6%). To me all these is due to very poor nutrition literacy, diet habits and lifestyle. I see people heaping their plates with food (esp rice) at weddings; people eating out everyday even till midnight; parents giving money to children to buy Grab food as an easy way out. ..... The story of the  VICTORY OF OUR LADY OF THE ROSARY at the Battle of Lepanto, on OCTOBER  7, 1571.
‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è
IN TIMES OF ACUTE DANGER AND HARDSHIP, WE MUST ALWAYS FLY INTO THE ARMS OF THE MOST POWERFUL MOTHER OF GOD AND TURN TO THE RECITATION OF HER HOLY ROSARY. The Battle of Lepanto is a great lesson of confidence for us today. 

When Saint Pius V became Pope, Christendom faced the perils perhaps unequaled in its history of continual conflict with the violent followers of Mohammed. All the information and intelligence that Pope Pius V had been gathering indicated that the Ottoman juggernaut was about to roll across the Mediterranean and adjacent lands, spearheaded by the Turkish fleet, with Italy and Rome as one of its target. (The Ottoman Empire is also historically known in Western Europe as the Turkish Empire)

Only Spain and Venice had the resources to resist, and they hated each other along with deep mistrust. Yet Saint Pius ‚Äî calling down divine grace as only a man of prayer could ‚Äî forged an alliance with them as the core of an organized fleet of over 200 galleys. With his considerable tact and diplomatic skills, he not only kept them unified, but he convinced them to attack the enveloping menace.

The Archbishop of Mexico had an exact copy of the HOLY IMAGE OF THE LADY OF GUADALUPE sent to King Philip II, who in turn gave it to Andrea Doria, one of the three principal admirals of the fleet, who placed it in his cabin. When the Armada went from file to line abreast and attacked on the morning of OCTOBER 7, 1571 the blue standard of OUR LADY OF GUADALUPE was also flying from the masthead of Don Juan‚Äôs flagship. 

Pope Pius V, a Dominican prelate before becoming a Pope, did what Catholics have always done in times of acute danger: FLY INTO THE ARMS OF THE MOST POWERFUL MOTHER OF GOD. As a follower of Saint Dominic, HE KNEW THE MOST EFFECTIVE MEANS OF IMPLORING HER HELP WAS THROUGH THE RECITATION OF THE HOLY ROSARY. He ordered all monasteries and convents in Rome to increase their prayers for the impending battle and organized ROSARY PROCESSIONS in which he, as sick as he was, participated. OUR LADY‚ÄôS PRESENCE THAT DAY WAS MORE ACUTELY FELT THROUGH THE HOLY ROSARY.

As the Christian fleet sailed toward the great clash, MASS WAS CELEBRATED AND THE ROSARY RECITED DAILY ON EACH VESSEL‚Ä¶.. THIS HEARTFELT REQUEST FOR DIVINE ASSISTANCE RESULTED IN A CRUSHING DEFEAT OF THE OTTOMANS AT LEPANTO THAT ENDED THEIR DOMINANCE AND CRUELTY IN THE MEDITERRANEAN. OCTOBER 7, 1571, WAS THE VICTORY OF OUR LADY OF THE MOST HOLY ROSARY, EVEN IF THE CHRISTIAN FLEET WAS GREATLY OUTNUMBERED BY THE OTTOMAN FLEET.
‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è‚ù§Ô∏è
TO CELEBRATE OUR LADY‚ÄôS INTERCESSION AND VICTORY, THE CHURCH HAS DESIGNATED OCTOBER 7 AS THE FEAST OF OUR LADY OF THE MOST HOLY ROSARY. Similar acknowledgement to the Blessed Virgin‚Äôs intercession through the Rosary were made when John Sobieski forced the Turks to lift the Siege of Vienna in 1683 and after the victory of Prince Eugene of Savoy at Temesvar in his successful campaign to remove the Ottomans from Europe in the next century.
